window.EQ_DATA["NVDA"] = {"ticker": "NVDA", "meta": {"ticker": "NVDA", "nome_empresa": "NVIDIA Corporation", "setor": "Semiconductors / AI Infrastructure", "geografia": "US", "moeda_reporte": "USD", "market_cap_usd_bn": "~4000", "shares_outstanding_bn": 24.3, "fiscal_year_end": "fim de janeiro (FY26 = year ended 2026-01-25)", "tags": ["setor/semis", "setor/ai-infra", "geografia/us", "moat/tecnologia", "moat/rede", "status/em_estudo"], "status_tese": "em_estudo", "data_criacao": "2026-04-20", "ultima_atualizacao": "2026-05-20"}, "views": {"ov": "<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h1>NVDA — NVIDIA Corporation</h1>\n<blockquote><strong>One-liner</strong>: Plataforma full-stack de data-center-scale AI infrastructure (GPU + CPU + networking + software <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=CUDA\" title=\"_concepts/CUDA\">CUDA</a>). Redefiniu-se de &quot;fabricante de chips&quot; para &quot;AI infrastructure company&quot; no ciclo atual.</blockquote></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>O negócio</h2><h3>O que a empresa faz</h3>\n<p>NVIDIA é uma <strong>AI infrastructure company em escala de data center</strong>. Oferece uma plataforma full-stack: GPUs (Blackwell Ultra atual, Rubin em ramp 2H FY27), CPUs (Grace, Vera), networking (NVLink, InfiniBand, Ethernet Spectrum-X, ConnectX, BlueField DPUs), sistemas (NVL72, rack-scale), e um stack de software enorme (CUDA + CUDA-X libs + AI Enterprise + Nemotron + Cosmos + Isaac GROOT + Omniverse + DRIVE).</p>\n<p>Fundada em 1993 (Californa, reincorporada em Delaware 1998). HQ: Santa Clara, CA.</p>\n<ul><li>Invenção do GPU: 1999</li><li>Lançamento do CUDA: 2006</li><li>Primeiro Tensor Core GPU: 2017</li><li>Aquisição da Mellanox: 2020 (virada pra data-center-scale via networking)</li><li>Grace CPU: 2023; Blackwell: 2024; Blackwell Ultra: FY26; Rubin: samples Fev/2026, produção 2H FY27</li><li>R&amp;D acumulado desde a fundação: $76.7B</li><li>78% dos supercomputers do TOP500 rodam em NVDA; 9 dos top 10 do Green500</li></ul>\n<h3>Segmentos contábeis (2)</h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Segmento</th><th>O que inclui</th><th>FY26 Revenue ($M)</th><th>% total</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Compute &amp; Networking</td><td>Data Center + Automotive</td><td>193,479</td><td>89.6%</td></tr><tr><td>Graphics</td><td>GeForce (gaming) + RTX PRO / Quadro (workstation)</td><td>22,459</td><td>10.4%</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Total</strong></td><td></td><td><strong>215,938</strong></td><td>100%</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Fonte: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q4-cfo-commentary\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY26-Q4-cfo-commentary\">Q4 FY26 CFO Commentary</a></p>\n<h3>Mercados finais (4) — breakdown por plataforma</h3>\n<p><strong>FY26 full year:</strong></p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Plataforma</th><th>FY26 ($M)</th><th>FY25 ($M)</th><th>YoY</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Data Center</td><td>193,737</td><td>115,186</td><td>+68%</td></tr><tr><td>— Compute</td><td>162,361</td><td>102,196</td><td>+59%</td></tr><tr><td>— Networking</td><td>31,376</td><td>12,990</td><td>+142%</td></tr><tr><td>Gaming</td><td>16,042</td><td>11,350</td><td>+41%</td></tr><tr><td>Professional Visualization</td><td>3,191</td><td>1,878</td><td>+70%</td></tr><tr><td>Automotive</td><td>2,349</td><td>1,694</td><td>+39%</td></tr><tr><td>OEM and Other</td><td>619</td><td>389</td><td>+59%</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Total</strong></td><td><strong>215,938</strong></td><td><strong>130,497</strong></td><td><strong>+65%</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p><strong>Q4 FY26:</strong></p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Plataforma</th><th>Q4 FY26 ($M)</th><th>Q4 FY25 ($M)</th><th>YoY</th><th>QoQ</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Data Center</td><td>62,314</td><td>35,580</td><td>+75%</td><td>+22%</td></tr><tr><td>— Compute</td><td>51,334</td><td>32,556</td><td>+58%</td><td>+19%</td></tr><tr><td>— Networking</td><td>10,980</td><td>3,024</td><td>+263%</td><td>+34%</td></tr><tr><td>Gaming</td><td>3,727</td><td>2,544</td><td>+47%</td><td>-13%</td></tr><tr><td>Professional Visualization</td><td>1,321</td><td>511</td><td>+159%</td><td>+74%</td></tr><tr><td>Automotive</td><td>604</td><td>570</td><td>+6%</td><td>+2%</td></tr><tr><td>OEM</td><td>161</td><td>126</td><td>—</td><td>—</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Total</strong></td><td><strong>68,127</strong></td><td><strong>39,331</strong></td><td><strong>+73%</strong></td><td><strong>+20%</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Fonte: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q4-cfo-commentary\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY26-Q4-cfo-commentary\">Q4 FY26 CFO Commentary</a></p>\n<h3>Concentração de clientes</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>Hyperscalers</strong> = <strong>slightly over 50%</strong> da DC revenue no Q4 FY26. Growth no Q4 foi <em>liderado pelos outros clientes</em> (diversificação). <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q4-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY26-Q4-earnings-call\">Q4 call</a></li><li><strong>Top 5 hyperscalers</strong> coletivamente: pouco mais de 50% do DC. CapEx 2026 consensual para os top 5: ~$700B (+$120B desde início de 2026).</li><li><strong>Sovereign AI</strong>: $30B+ em FY26, <strong>+3x YoY</strong>. Clientes principais: Canadá, França, Holanda, Singapura, UK.</li><li><strong>Physical AI</strong> (auto + robotics): $6B+ em FY26.</li></ul>\n<h3>Geografia</h3>\n<p>Paulo: isso ainda não está extraído do 10-K. Provavelmente tem split US / Singapura / Taiwan / China. <strong>[ ] A investigar no 10-K FY26.</strong></p></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Management e governança</h2><p><em>Análise profunda na Pergunta 3.</em> Snapshot:</p>\n<ul><li><strong>CEO</strong>: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=jensen-huang\" title=\"_people/jensen-huang\">Jensen Huang</a> (Jen-Hsun Huang), co-founder, desde 1993. Ainda muito operacional — faz keynote das earnings calls.</li><li><strong>CFO</strong>: Colette Kress (Chief Financial Officer &amp; Executive Vice President).</li><li><strong>VP IR</strong>: Toshiya Hari.</li><li><strong>Skin in the game</strong>: 1.0B shares detidas por diretores e executivos (declaração de julho 2025) de 24.3B totais ≈ 4%. Jensen é a maioria disso. <strong>[ ] Confirmar ownership exato no proxy FY26</strong> — ainda não está no vault.</li><li><strong>Retorno ao acionista FY26</strong>: $41.1B ($40.1B buyback + $974M dividendos) = <strong>43% do FCF</strong>. Dividend yield minúsculo. Buyback é o canal dominante.</li></ul></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Financeiros (snapshot)</h2><p><strong>FY26 full year (ended Jan 25, 2026):</strong></p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Métrica</th><th>FY26 GAAP</th><th>FY26 Non-GAAP</th><th>FY25 GAAP</th><th>YoY GAAP</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Revenue</td><td>$215,938M</td><td>$215,938M</td><td>$130,497M</td><td>+65%</td></tr><tr><td>Gross margin</td><td>71.1%</td><td>71.3%</td><td>75.0%</td><td>-3.9 pts</td></tr><tr><td>Operating income</td><td>$130,387M</td><td>$137,300M</td><td>$81,453M</td><td>+60%</td></tr><tr><td>Net income</td><td>$120,067M</td><td>$116,997M</td><td>$72,880M</td><td>+65%</td></tr><tr><td>Diluted EPS</td><td>$4.90</td><td>$4.77</td><td>$2.94</td><td>+67%</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Observação: gross margin <strong>caiu 3.9 pts em FY26 GAAP</strong> (FY25 teve mix mais favorável). Isso reflete o ramp de Blackwell — margens tipicamente comprimem na introdução e depois reexpandem. Q4 FY26 GAAP GM já voltou a 75.0%. Guidance Q1 FY27 = 74.9-75.0%.</p>\n<p><strong>Balanço / liquidez (Q4 FY26):</strong></p>\n<ul><li>Cash + marketable securities: $62.6B</li><li>Supply commitments totais: $95.2B (≈ 44% da receita FY26)</li><li>Multi-year cloud service agreements: $27.0B (para R&amp;D)</li><li>Inventory: $21.4B (+8% QoQ)</li><li>Free cash flow FY26: $97B (margem FCF ≈ 45%)</li><li>Shares outstanding Feb 20, 2026: 24.3B (caindo — buybacks)</li><li>Weighted avg diluted shares FY26: 24.5B vs 24.8B em FY25 (ritmo de buyback modesto em % por causa do crescimento de valor)</li></ul>\n<p><strong>🆕 Q1 FY27 (quarter ended 26-Abr-2026 — <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY27-Q1-10-Q\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY27-Q1-10-Q\">10-Q</a>):</strong></p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Métrica</th><th>Q1 FY27 GAAP</th><th>Q1 FY26 GAAP</th><th>YoY</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Revenue</td><td>$81,615M</td><td>$44,062M</td><td>+85%</td></tr><tr><td>Gross margin</td><td>74.9%</td><td>60.5%</td><td>+14,4 pts</td></tr><tr><td>Operating income</td><td>$53,536M</td><td>$21,638M</td><td>+147%</td></tr><tr><td>Net income</td><td>$58,321M</td><td>$18,775M</td><td>+211%</td></tr><tr><td>Diluted EPS</td><td>$2.39</td><td>$0.76</td><td>+214%</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<ul><li><strong>Balanço (26-Abr-2026)</strong>: total assets <strong>$259,5B</strong>; shareholders&#x27; equity <strong>$195,5B</strong>; dívida bruta só <strong>~$8,5B</strong> (net cash enorme; commercial paper $25B capacity, zero usado).</li><li>Cash + marketable debt <strong>$50,3B</strong> + marketable equity securities <strong>$30,2B</strong> + <strong>non-marketable securities $43,4B</strong> (saltou de $22,3B — ver seção Q1 FY27).</li><li><strong>FCF Q1 FY27: $48,6B</strong>; OCF $50,3B. Inventory $25,8B.</li><li>Commitments: supply <strong>$119B</strong> + multi-year cloud <strong>$30B</strong> + investment commitments <strong>$27B</strong> + future leases a iniciar <strong>$32,4B</strong>.</li><li>⚠️ <strong>FY27 é 53-week year; Q4 FY27 será 14-week quarter</strong> — ajustar comparações QoQ/YoY do Q4.</li></ul></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Catalisadores</h2><ul><li><strong><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=Vera-Rubin\" title=\"_concepts/Vera-Rubin\">Vera Rubin</a></strong>: samples despachados em Fev/2026, produção 2H FY27. Promessa de 10x redução em cost per token vs Blackwell.</li><li><strong>NVLink Fusion</strong>: expansão do ecossistema com custom silicon (parceria AWS anunciada).</li><li><strong>Sovereign AI</strong>: base de $30B+, em expansão &quot;&gt;= AI infra market&quot;.</li><li><strong>Physical AI / robotics</strong>: Cosmos + Isaac GROOT + parcerias Boston Dynamics, Caterpillar, LG, NEURA, Siemens, Synopsys, Dassault Systèmes.</li><li><strong>Automotive Alpamayo</strong>: primeiro carro (Mercedes-Benz CLA) na estrada &quot;em breve&quot;.</li></ul></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Update May/2026 — GTC 2026 disclosure: NVDA vendendo pure CPU server racks (via Fubon)</h2><p>Adicionado <strong>2026-05-08</strong> via cross-reference do <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2026-05-Fubon-Server-CPU-Shortage\" title=\"raw-md/TSM/2026-05-Fubon-Server-CPU-Shortage\">Fubon Server Outlook 8-May-2026</a> que disclosed um sinal estratégico relevante de NVDA do <strong>GTC 2026</strong>:</p>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;We also learned from GTC 2026 that <strong>nVidia will sell total solutions starting with its next generation AI servers, i.e., not just GPU servers but also pure CPU server racks</strong>.&quot;</em> — Fubon Research</blockquote>\n<h3>🔥 Significado estratégico</h3>\n<ol><li><strong>Mudança de modelo</strong>: NVDA tradicionalmente vendia GPU + sistema (DGX, HGX) com CPU sourced de Intel/AMD. Agora vende <strong>rack completo incluindo CPU</strong>.</li><li><strong>Não significa que NVDA fabrica CPU própria</strong>: a CPU continua sendo Intel/AMD/Grace (NVDA&#x27;s próprio ARM CPU). Mas o <strong>rack completo é vendido como solução NVDA</strong>, não componente isolado.</li><li><strong>Captura mais $$/rack</strong> — NVDA agora se beneficia da margem de socket, networking, cooling e CPU. Antes ficava com cliente/ODM.</li><li><strong>Comoditiza relacionamento ODM</strong>: hyperscalers que antes compravam GPU NVDA + integravam (via Wiwynn/SuperMicro/Quanta) agora podem comprar racks turnkey direto da NVDA.</li></ol>\n<h3>Implicações para tese NVDA</h3>\n<p>✓ <strong>TAM expansion</strong>: NVDA passa a capturar valor que antes ficava em system integrators / ODMs ✓ <strong>Validação rack-scale strategy</strong>: começou com NVL72 (Blackwell), agora estende ao próximo gen ✓ <strong>Margem mix</strong>: CPU e cooling têm margem inferior a GPU, mas NVDA captura escala de software/networking ⚠️ <strong>Stress nos ODMs</strong>: Wiwynn (6669 TT, Hon Hai 2317 TT, Quanta 2382 TT) podem ser <strong>deslocados ou recatalogados como contract manufacturers</strong> sob marca NVDA ⚠️ <strong>Conflito potential com AMD/Intel</strong>: se NVDA vende rack com CPU Intel/AMD pré-integrada, pode ter dependência conflituosa (NVDA queria empurrar Grace?)</p>\n<h3>Combina com tese Agentic AI (CPU shift)</h3>\n<p>A entrada de NVDA em pure CPU server racks <strong>não é coincidência</strong> — é resposta direta à mudança Agentic AI documentada em <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=agentic-AI-CPU-shift\" title=\"_concepts/agentic-AI-CPU-shift\">agentic-AI-CPU-shift</a>:</p>\n<ul><li>CPU virou orchestrator (90% do runtime em workloads agênticos)</li><li>Hyperscalers precisam de <strong>bundle CPU + GPU + networking</strong> otimizado pra agentic</li><li>NVDA detém a maior parte do moat de networking (NVLink, InfiniBand, Spectrum-X) → vende stack full</li></ul>\n<p>→ <strong>NVDA NÃO está respondendo a ASIC ameaça</strong>: está <strong>expandindo TAM</strong> indo pra layer adjacente (CPU racks). É positivo pra tese, não negativo.</p>\n<h3>Cross-references</h3>\n<ul><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=agentic-AI-CPU-shift\" title=\"_concepts/agentic-AI-CPU-shift\">agentic-AI-CPU-shift</a> — entity page do tema</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=TSM\" title=\"wiki/TSM\">TSM</a> — beneficiário direto da AMD Venice em N2 (CPU principal nessas racks NVDA)</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=ASIC-vs-GPU\" title=\"_concepts/ASIC-vs-GPU\">ASIC-vs-GPU</a> — Agentic AI requer CPU + GPU + ASIC; NVDA pivot para CPU rack defende a posição contra custom silicon dos hyperscalers</li></ul></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Update May/2026 — Inference Shift framing (Ben Thompson / Stratechery)</h2><p>Adicionado <strong>2026-05-11</strong> via ingestão de <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2026-05-11-Stratechery-Inference-Shift\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/2026-05-11-Stratechery-Inference-Shift\">Stratechery &amp;quot;The Inference Shift&amp;quot; (11-May-2026)</a> — análise estrutural cross-company de Ben Thompson disparada pelo IPO da <strong>Cerebras</strong> (price range raised $115-125 → $150-160; 30M shares).</p>\n<h3>Framework central — três mercados, três arquiteturas</h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Mercado</th><th>Hardware-fit</th><th>Status NVDA</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Training</strong></td><td>GPU + HBM + NVLink + networking</td><td>🟢 Dominante, <strong>continua assim</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Answer inference</strong> (humano no loop, latency matters)</td><td>GPU OU specialized SRAM-heavy (Cerebras WSE-3, Groq LPU)</td><td>🟡 Compete com chips especializados; mercado <strong>menor</strong> (bounded por humanos × tempo)</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Agentic inference</strong> (sem humano, memory &gt; speed)</td><td>Memory hierarchy + good-enough compute + CPU orchestrator</td><td>🟠 <strong>GPU &quot;unbundled&quot;</strong> — premium NVDA menos justificado; <strong>mas largest market by far</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<h3>Os 3 estágios da inference (BT detalha)</h3>\n<ol><li><strong>Prefill</strong> — paralelizável, <strong>compute matters</strong> (favorece GPU)</li><li><strong>Decode parte 1 — KV cache read</strong>: serial, bandwidth matters, memory variável crescente</li><li><strong>Decode parte 2 — feed-forward over weights</strong>: serial, bandwidth matters, memory fixa (= tamanho modelo)</li></ol>\n<p>GPU acomoda os 3 (compute + HBM + networking). Mas em workloads agentic com memory hierarchy sofisticada (KV cache + host memory + SSDs + databases + logs + embeddings + object stores), <strong>dá pra desagregar</strong>: compute mais barato, memory tier mais barata, <strong>CPUs robustas pra tool use</strong> (BT: <em>&quot;speed of CPUs for things like tool use may matter more than speed of GPUs&quot;</em>).</p>\n<h3>Cerebras WSE-3 — comparação direta vs H100</h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th></th><th>Cerebras WSE-3</th><th>NVDA H100</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Memory</td><td><strong>44GB SRAM</strong></td><td>80GB HBM</td></tr><tr><td>Bandwidth</td><td><strong>21 PB/s</strong></td><td>3.35 TB/s</td></tr><tr><td>Multiple</td><td>0.55x mem, <strong>6,000x bw</strong></td><td>baseline</td></tr><tr><td>Limit</td><td>Modelos/KV cache que não cabem em SRAM</td><td>Generalist tradeoff</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Cerebras = <strong>target market answer inference</strong> (chatbots latency-sensitive, AI wearables voice). <strong>Não compete com NVDA em training nem agentic</strong> — apenas no nicho specialized. Yields baixos em whole-wafer-as-chip drive up cost.</p>\n<h3>Cross-validation — NVDA reconhece o shift</h3>\n<p>✓ <strong>Dynamo framework</strong>: NVDA&#x27;s inference framework que disaggregate prefill / decode-KV / decode-feedforward em hardware diferente — exatamente o que BT prevê.</p>\n<p>✓ <strong>Pure CPU server racks (GTC 2026)</strong>: cross-link com Update May/2026 abaixo — NVDA vendendo standalone memory + CPU racks pra keep GPUs ocupadas com KV cache massivo + tool use. <strong>NÃO é resposta a ASIC threat — é resposta ao agentic inference shift.</strong></p>\n<p>✓ <strong>Colossus 1 / Anthropic deal</strong>: SpaceX construiu Colossus 1 (220k+ NVDA GPUs, 300+ MW) para training de xAI; <strong>agora arrendado integralmente pra Anthropic inference</strong> (Claude Pro/Max subscribers). Reafirma BT: <em>&quot;what works for training works for inference&quot;</em> — flexibilidade GPU é vantagem real enquanto agentic memory-hierarchy arch não viabiliza.</p>\n<h3>Implicações concretas pra tese NVDA</h3>\n<p><strong>Bull case (intacto)</strong>:</p>\n<ul><li>Training permanece NVDA-dominated (status quo + scaling laws + chip-to-chip networking moat)</li><li>Answer inference: NVDA + chips specialized split — mas mercado bounded</li><li>Bridge demand sólida — Colossus 1 / Anthropic mostra que GPUs construídas para training rebalanceiam pra inference sem reconfiguração</li><li>Dynamo + CPU racks = NVDA capturing TAM adjacente (memory + CPU layer)</li></ul>\n<p><strong>Bear case (BT articula explicitamente)</strong>:</p>\n<ul><li>Agentic inference = largest market by far → NVDA premium de latência (HBM, NVLink, networking) <strong>menos worth paying</strong></li><li>Hyperscalers preferem <strong>simplicidade + custo</strong> em agentic → vetor pró-ASIC custom + commodity DRAM (Micron/Samsung) + CPU robusto (AMD/Intel/Graviton)</li><li><strong>China</strong>: sanções US falham em bloquear agentic AI chinês porque agentic não precisa de leading-edge (Huawei Ascend &quot;good enough&quot; + CPUs domésticos + CXMT DRAM)</li><li><strong>Jensen &quot;Moore&#x27;s Law is Dead&quot;</strong> → BT inverte: <em>&quot;the way we get more compute is by realizing that the compute we have is already good enough&quot;</em></li></ul>\n<h3>Catalisadores adicionais a monitorar</h3>\n<ul><li>[ ] Cerebras pós-IPO: market reception sinaliza apetite por answer-inference specialized chips</li><li>[ ] Anthropic / OpenAI capacity deals com 3rd-party DCs (Colossus 1 = primeiro grande) — implica que arquiteturas agentic memory-hierarchy ainda <strong>não existem em produção em escala</strong>, portanto GPU rebalance segue caminho</li><li>[ ] NVDA Dynamo adoption rate em hyperscalers (Q1-Q2 FY27 earnings calls)</li><li>[ ] Standalone memory/CPU rack pricing + volume (próxima earnings) — proxy pra &quot;agentic shift defense&quot; funcionando</li></ul>\n<h3>Cross-references</h3>\n<ul><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=agentic-AI-CPU-shift\" title=\"_concepts/agentic-AI-CPU-shift\">agentic-AI-CPU-shift</a> — framework &quot;answer vs agentic&quot; expandido + Fubon CPU shortage convergente</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=ASIC-vs-GPU\" title=\"_concepts/ASIC-vs-GPU\">ASIC-vs-GPU</a> — heterogeneous compute como reformulação do debate</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=hyperscaler-capex\" title=\"_concepts/hyperscaler-capex\">hyperscaler-capex</a> — Anthropic-SpaceX Colossus 1 data point</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=CUDA\" title=\"_concepts/CUDA\">CUDA</a> — moat ainda relevante em training; em agentic, valor de CUDA muda (importa mais pra CPU orchestrator que pra inferência throughput?)</li></ul></section>\n<details class=\"notes-appendix\"><summary>Notas, pendências e changelog</summary><section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Pontos em aberto / a investigar</h2><ul><li>[ ] Breakdown geográfico completo de receita (Item 7 do 10-K ou nota de segmentos).</li><li>[ ] Exposição exata a China: H20 adjustments ($4.5B Q1 FY26), H200 status atual, revenue histórica.</li><li>[ ] Ownership exato de insiders: confirmar no proxy FY26 (não disponível no vault ainda).</li><li>[ ] Stock-based compensation — impacto do reinclusão no non-GAAP em Q1 FY27 nos múltiplos reportados pelo Street.</li><li>[ ] Sensibilidade a CapEx de cada hyperscaler (top 5 individualizados). Usar <code>F:\\...\\NVDA\\Cópia de Hypsercale CapEx Spending Lease Analysis.xlsx</code>.</li><li>[ ] Comparação ASIC vs GPU: TPO (total perf + TCO + ecossistema). Research de <code>A Deep Dive on Inference Semiconductors</code> (Eric Flaningam) e <code>AI Hardware Net Assessment — Why Huawei Can&#x27;t Catch Nvidia</code> são candidatos para Fase 2.</li><li>[ ] Consenso de revenue/EPS FY27/FY28 — usar para calibrar expectativas implícitas no preço.</li></ul></section><section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Histórico de atualizações</h2><ul><li><strong>2026-05-11</strong>: ⚠️ <strong>Stratechery &quot;Inference Shift&quot; (Ben Thompson) ingerido</strong> — framework conceitual &quot;answer inference vs agentic inference&quot; formalizado. Adicionado novo risco estrutural &quot;Inference shift — premium de latência da NVDA unbundle em agentic&quot; + nova seção &quot;Update May/2026 — Inference Shift framing&quot;. Cross-references atualizadas em <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=agentic-AI-CPU-shift\" title=\"_concepts/agentic-AI-CPU-shift\">agentic-AI-CPU-shift</a> (nova seção BT framework), <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=ASIC-vs-GPU\" title=\"_concepts/ASIC-vs-GPU\">ASIC-vs-GPU</a> (nova seção heterogeneous compute), <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=hyperscaler-capex\" title=\"_concepts/hyperscaler-capex\">hyperscaler-capex</a> (novo data point Colossus 1 / Anthropic 220k GPUs 300MW). Bear case BT: NVDA premium de latência menos justificado em agentic (largest future market). Mitigantes: Dynamo framework, GTC 2026 CPU racks já antecipam; training + answer inference permanecem NVDA-led; Colossus 1 prova flexibilidade GPU training→inference.</li><li><strong>2026-05-08</strong>: ⚠️ <strong>GTC 2026 disclosure ingerido via Fubon Server Outlook</strong>: NVDA vai vender <strong>pure CPU server racks</strong> começando com next gen AI servers — não apenas GPU servers. Mudança estrutural rack-scale strategy. NVDA captura $$ adicional por rack (CPU + cooling + networking layer); ODMs (Wiwynn/Hon Hai/Quanta) podem ser comoditizados ou virar contract manufacturers de marca NVDA. Conexão direta com <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=agentic-AI-CPU-shift\" title=\"_concepts/agentic-AI-CPU-shift\">Agentic AI CPU shift</a> — NVDA pivota para CPU rack porque Agentic AI requer GPU+CPU bundle otimizado. Cross-link em <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=TSM\" title=\"wiki/TSM\">TSM</a> (AMD Venice em N2 = CPU principal das racks NVDA).</li><li><strong>2026-04-20</strong>: wiki criada a partir da Fase 1 de conversão (16 docs SEC FY26 + GTC 2025 keynote). Conteúdo inicial: segmentos, P&amp;L snapshot, moat (hipóteses), riscos declarados, guidance Q1 FY27. Análises profundas (Perguntas 1/3/4) ainda a rodar.</li><li><strong>2026-04-20</strong>: refatorada para padrão Karpathy — extraídas entity pages <code><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=CUDA\" title=\"_concepts/CUDA\">CUDA</a></code>, <code><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=NVLink\" title=\"_concepts/NVLink\">NVLink</a></code>, <code><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=Blackwell\" title=\"_concepts/Blackwell\">Blackwell</a></code>, <code><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=Vera-Rubin\" title=\"_concepts/Vera-Rubin\">Vera-Rubin</a></code>, <code><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=CoWoS\" title=\"_concepts/CoWoS\">CoWoS</a></code>, <code><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=hyperscaler-capex\" title=\"_concepts/hyperscaler-capex\">hyperscaler-capex</a></code>, <code><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=ASIC-vs-GPU\" title=\"_concepts/ASIC-vs-GPU\">ASIC-vs-GPU</a></code> e <code><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=jensen-huang\" title=\"_people/jensen-huang\">Jensen Huang</a></code>. Linkada no <code><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=INDEX\" title=\"INDEX\">INDEX</a></code>.</li><li><strong>2026-04-23</strong>: <strong>Fase 2 ingestão</strong> — 3 10-Ks históricos FY23/FY24/FY25 + 4 earnings calls FactSet FY26 Q1-Q4 convertidos via OCR (rapidocr-onnxruntime). Adicionada seção &quot;Evolução histórica FY21 → FY26&quot; com tabela de revenue por segmento + EPS e análise de trajetória. Sem marks [STALE] aplicados — conteúdo FY26 existente permanece válido; seção histórica é aditiva.</li><li><strong>2026-05-19</strong>: ingerido <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2026-05-11-MS-Agentic-AI-Surge\" title=\"raw-md/TSM/2026-05-11-MS-Agentic-AI-Surge\">Morgan Stanley &amp;quot;Agentic AI — The Surge Begins&amp;quot; 11-May-2026</a>. Leitura para NVDA: (1) <strong>agentic NÃO reduz demanda por GPU</strong> — MS reforça &quot;stay full-stack&quot;: AI DC precisa de GPU racks (dense model compute) <strong>+</strong> novos racks de CPU agentic (orchestration) — supportive da tese GPU; (2) MS pareia exposição preferida de CPU como <strong>&quot;NVDA-Intel&quot;</strong> e cita <strong>Xeon 6 como host CPU do NVIDIA DGX Rubin NVL8</strong> — NVDA capturando o host layer junto; (3) <strong>CPU:GPU ratio ramp 1:2 → 2:1 em 2030</strong> (bull) = mais CPU por DC, vetor de comoditização parcial do relacionamento (bear de <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=agentic-AI-CPU-shift\" title=\"_concepts/agentic-AI-CPU-shift\">agentic-AI-CPU-shift</a>). Net: report é neutro-a-positivo p/ NVDA no curto (GPU demand intacta) mas quantifica o shift de gasto incremental p/ CPU/memória — acompanhar Dynamo + pure-CPU racks como defesa. Detalhe cross-company em <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=agentic-AI-CPU-shift\" title=\"_concepts/agentic-AI-CPU-shift\">agentic-AI-CPU-shift</a> / <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=hyperscaler-capex\" title=\"_concepts/hyperscaler-capex\">hyperscaler-capex</a>.</li><li><strong>2026-05-20</strong>: ✅ <strong>Q1 FY27 earnings call ingerido</strong> (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY27-Q1-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY27-Q1-earnings-call\">FY27-Q1-earnings-call</a> — Bloomberg Live Transcript do dia, trimestre encerrado 27-Abr-2026). Wiki atualizada com nova seção &quot;Q1 FY27 — earnings call 20-May-2026&quot;. <strong>Disclosures materiais</strong>: (1) <strong>Revenue Q1 US$82bn (+85% YoY, +20% QoQ)</strong>, DC US$75bn (+92% YoY), DC networking ~3x YoY (US$15bn) — recorde absoluto de increment sequencial (US$13.5bn); (2) <strong>Novo framework de reporting</strong>: Data Center (Hyperscale + ACIE) + Edge Computing — separa hyperscaler (~US$1T capex 2027) da ACIE (250k empresas, 100% inferência NVDA, ~US$50T GDP/40 países sovereign +80% YoY); (3) <strong>Vera CPU</strong>: TAM novo <strong>US$200bn</strong>, custom Arm cores, 1.5x perf/core, <strong>agentic CPU purpose-built</strong>; ~US$20bn visibilidade FY27 standalone (NÃO incluso no US$1T Blackwell+Rubin = upside puro); 4 use cases (Rubin pair / standalone / +CX9 storage / +CX9 security); (4) <strong>Vera Rubin shipments Q3 FY27</strong>, ramp Q4+Q1FY28; 7 chips/5 racks; <strong>35x inference throughput, 10x AI factory revenue vs Blackwell</strong>; <strong>Google A5X early adopter até 960k Rubin GPUs</strong>; &quot;every frontier model company will jump from get-go&quot;; (5) <strong>MSFT Fairwater live ahead of schedule</strong> (hundreds of thousands Blackwell), <strong>AWS adding &gt;1M Blackwell+Rubin</strong> + Spectrum collab, <strong>Google Blackwell + confidential computing</strong>; (6) <strong>Anthropic adicionada à parceria</strong> (coverage era &quot;largely zero&quot; antes); frontier labs em NVDA agora incluem MSL/SpaceX/xAI/Reflection/Cursor; (7) <strong>AI infra spending US$3-4T/ano end of decade</strong>, hyperscale CapEx <strong>&gt;US$1T em 2027</strong>; H100 cloud +20% YTD, A100 +15% YTD; (8) <strong>Q2 outlook US$91bn ±2%</strong>; OpEx FY27 cresce upper-40s YoY; tax 16-18%; (9) <strong>Capital allocation</strong>: dividendo <strong>25x ($0.01→$0.25)</strong> + <strong>US$80bn buyback novo</strong> (sobre US$39bn remanescentes) + 50% FCF return FY27; (10) <strong>MLPerf sweep</strong> Blackwell Ultra; GB300 = 2.7x throughput / 60% cost-per-token reduction vs 6 meses; (11) <strong>Edge US$6.4bn (+29% YoY)</strong>, physical AI &gt;US$9bn L12M, Uber Robotaxi 30 cidades/4 continentes até 2028; (12) <strong>China DC compute = NÃO no outlook</strong> (consistente Q4). Cross-implications atualizadas: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=Vera-Rubin\" title=\"_concepts/Vera-Rubin\">Vera-Rubin</a> (TAM + ramp), <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=Blackwell\" title=\"_concepts/Blackwell\">Blackwell</a> (Fairwater + MLPerf), <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=agentic-AI-CPU-shift\" title=\"_concepts/agentic-AI-CPU-shift\">agentic-AI-CPU-shift</a> (NVDA self-confirms $200B agentic CPU TAM), <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=hyperscaler-capex\" title=\"_concepts/hyperscaler-capex\">hyperscaler-capex</a> ($1T 2027 / $3-4T 2030 reaffirmed), <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=ASIC-vs-GPU\" title=\"_concepts/ASIC-vs-GPU\">ASIC-vs-GPU</a> (coexistência confirmada apesar Trainium/Maia/TPU). <strong>Implicação central</strong>: Jensen <em>&quot;Demand has gone parabolic. Agentic AI has arrived.&quot;</em> — NVDA passa a competir em CPU agentic; ACIE como growth driver separado do CapEx hyperscaler; Vera = upside puro acima do US$1T Blackwell+Rubin.</li><li><strong>2026-05-20 (later)</strong>: ✅ <strong>CFO Commentary + Revenue-by-Market trend (recast 9 tri) ingeridos</strong> (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY27-Q1-cfo-commentary\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY27-Q1-cfo-commentary\">FY27-Q1-cfo-commentary</a> + <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY27-Q1-revenue-by-market-trend\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY27-Q1-revenue-by-market-trend\">FY27-Q1-revenue-by-market-trend</a>). Refinada a seção &quot;Q1 FY27&quot; com números oficiais precisos (vs rounded da call). <strong>Datapoints novos não cobertos na call</strong>: (1) <strong>Compute &amp; Networking segment +88% YoY (US$74,550M)</strong> vs Graphics +58% (P&amp;L statutory); (2) <strong>DC networking +199% YoY</strong> (=3x literal, vs &quot;nearly tripled&quot; da call) — Spectrum-X + InfiniBand XDR contribuição extraordinária; (3) <strong>Zero Hopper shipments p/ China em Q1 FY27 vs US$4.6bn em Q1 FY26</strong> — base de comparação YoY agora limpa; (4) <strong>GM Q1 FY26 60.5% foi deprimida por US$4.5B H20 charge</strong>; Q1 FY27 H20 = zero → toda margem expansion YoY é clean; (5) <strong>Mudança de metodologia non-GAAP</strong>: a partir de Q1 FY27 SBC NÃO é mais excluído do non-GAAP; históricos recast — comparações precisam usar nova base; (6) <strong>Equity securities gains não-cash US$15.9bn no Q1</strong> drive o delta GAAP NI ($58.3B) vs non-GAAP NI ($45.5B); (7) <strong>Multi-year cloud service commitments US$30.0bn</strong> (linha separada do supply-related US$119bn) — <strong>NVDA é cliente de cloud também</strong> em escala material p/ &quot;growing R&amp;D needs&quot;; (8) <strong>Reconciliação do US$145bn supply</strong> da call: inventário US$25.8bn + commitments US$119.0bn ≈ US$145bn; (9) <strong>Recast 9-quarter table</strong>: ACIE volátil (caiu 20% QoQ em FY26 Q2) mas inflectiu <strong>+31% QoQ em FY27 Q1</strong>; <strong>Hyperscale ≈ ACIE pela 1ª vez</strong> (37.9 vs 37.4 US$bn); (10) <strong>Tax rate Q1 FY27</strong>: GAAP 16.6% / non-GAAP 16.0%; (11) <strong>OCF US$50.3bn / FCF US$48.6bn</strong> (vs Q4 US$36.2bn / US$34.9bn). Conceito atualizado: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=Blackwell\" title=\"_concepts/Blackwell\">Blackwell</a> (DC networking +199%, ramp Blackwell 300 explicitamente atribuído). Implicação: a tese fica mais robusta — margem expansion YoY é orgânica (não só base effect do H20), e DC networking quase triplicando expõe um vetor de mix-shift (Spectrum-X + InfiniBand XDR + NVLink) que o framing de &quot;GPU vendor&quot; subestima.</li><li><strong>2026-05-21</strong>: ✅ <strong>Form 10-Q Q1 FY27 ingerido</strong> (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY27-Q1-10-Q\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY27-Q1-10-Q\">FY27-Q1-10-Q</a> — SEC, quarter ended 26-Abr-2026). Fonte canônica GAAP; adicionada subseção &quot;10-Q — disclosures novas (Notes)&quot; + snapshot Q1 FY27 em Financeiros. <strong>Datapoints só do 10-Q</strong>: (1) <strong>balanço</strong>: total assets $259,5B, equity $195,5B, dívida bruta ~$8,5B (net cash enorme); (2) <strong>segment OI</strong>: Compute &amp; Networking $53,3B (+142% YoY); (3) <strong>geografia</strong>: EUA 78% / China $4,55B (gaming/workstation, não DC); concentração de clientes subiu p/ <strong>~54% em 3 clientes diretos</strong>; (4) <strong>🔥 non-marketable securities $22,3B → $43,4B em 1 tri</strong>, com <strong>$18,6B investidos em private AI cos / infra funds</strong> — 10-Q diz explicitamente que incluem &quot;AI model makers that may indirectly purchase our products&quot; = <strong>financiamento circular</strong>; (5) <strong>future leases a iniciar $32,4B</strong> (DCs p/ R&amp;D, FY27-33) — NVDA construindo compute próprio; (6) <strong>53-week FY27, Q4 = 14 semanas</strong> (comparabilidade); (7) <strong>RPO só $2,6B</strong> — NVDA vende à vista, não tem backlog contratado; (8) buyback Q1: 84% das ações compradas no fim do quarter (23-Mar a 26-Abr) a ~$185; (9) litígio securities-class-action 2018 com classe certificada em Mar-2026 (risco-cauda); (10) IRS examinando FY23-FY24. Conceito atualizado: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=hyperscaler-capex\" title=\"_concepts/hyperscaler-capex\">hyperscaler-capex</a> (financiamento circular). Implicação: balanço sobra-caixa + capacidade de auto-financiar ecosystem; mas concentração de clientes e financiamento circular são pontos de atenção de qualidade-de-receita.</li></ul></section><section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Fontes no vault</h2><h3>Documentos primários (convertidos — Fase 1)</h3>\n<p><strong>10-Ks (histórico):</strong></p>\n<ul><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY23-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY23-10-K\">FY23-10-K</a> <em>(ingested 2026-04-23)</em></li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY24-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY24-10-K\">FY24-10-K</a> <em>(ingested 2026-04-23)</em></li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY25-10-K\">FY25-10-K</a> <em>(ingested 2026-04-23)</em></li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY26-10-K\">FY26-10-K</a></li></ul>\n<p><strong>10-Qs (FY26):</strong></p>\n<ul><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-10-Q\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY26-Q1-10-Q\">FY26-Q1-10-Q</a></li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q2-10-Q\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY26-Q2-10-Q\">FY26-Q2-10-Q</a></li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q3-10-Q\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY26-Q3-10-Q\">FY26-Q3-10-Q</a></li></ul>\n<p><strong>Earnings calls (FY26) — NVIDIA IR official:</strong></p>\n<ul><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY26-Q1-earnings-call\">FY26-Q1-earnings-call</a></li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q2-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY26-Q2-earnings-call\">FY26-Q2-earnings-call</a></li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q3-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY26-Q3-earnings-call\">FY26-Q3-earnings-call</a></li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q4-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY26-Q4-earnings-call\">FY26-Q4-earnings-call</a></li></ul>\n<p><strong>Earnings calls (FY26) — FactSet CallStreet (Corrected Transcripts):</strong> <em>(ingested 2026-04-23)</em></p>\n<ul><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-earnings-call-factset\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY26-Q1-earnings-call-factset\">FY26-Q1-earnings-call-factset</a></li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q2-earnings-call-factset\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY26-Q2-earnings-call-factset\">FY26-Q2-earnings-call-factset</a></li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q3-earnings-call-factset\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY26-Q3-earnings-call-factset\">FY26-Q3-earnings-call-factset</a></li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q4-earnings-call-factset\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY26-Q4-earnings-call-factset\">FY26-Q4-earnings-call-factset</a></li></ul>\n<p><strong>CFO commentaries (FY26):</strong></p>\n<ul><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-cfo-commentary\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY26-Q1-cfo-commentary\">FY26-Q1-cfo-commentary</a></li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q2-cfo-commentary\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY26-Q2-cfo-commentary\">FY26-Q2-cfo-commentary</a></li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q3-cfo-commentary\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY26-Q3-cfo-commentary\">FY26-Q3-cfo-commentary</a></li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q4-cfo-commentary\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY26-Q4-cfo-commentary\">FY26-Q4-cfo-commentary</a></li></ul>\n<p><strong>Quarterly presentations (FY26):</strong></p>\n<ul><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-quarterly-presentation\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY26-Q1-quarterly-presentation\">FY26-Q1-quarterly-presentation</a></li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q2-quarterly-presentation\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY26-Q2-quarterly-presentation\">FY26-Q2-quarterly-presentation</a></li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q3-quarterly-presentation\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY26-Q3-quarterly-presentation\">FY26-Q3-quarterly-presentation</a></li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q4-quarterly-presentation\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY26-Q4-quarterly-presentation\">FY26-Q4-quarterly-presentation</a></li></ul>\n<p><strong>Eventos:</strong></p>\n<ul><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2025-03-GTC-keynote\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/2025-03-GTC-keynote\">2025-03-GTC-keynote</a></li></ul>\n<p><strong>Research / análise terceiros:</strong></p>\n<ul><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2026-05-11-Stratechery-Inference-Shift\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/2026-05-11-Stratechery-Inference-Shift\">2026-05-11-Stratechery-Inference-Shift</a> — Ben Thompson, Stratechery (11-May-2026): answer vs agentic inference framework, Cerebras WSE-3 specs, NVDA Dynamo + CPU racks, Anthropic-SpaceX Colossus 1 deal</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY27-Q1-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY27-Q1-earnings-call\">FY27-Q1-earnings-call</a> — Q1 FY27 earnings call, 20-May-2026 (Bloomberg Live Transcript): Vera US$200bn TAM, novo framework Hyperscale+ACIE+Edge, MSFT Fairwater live, AWS &gt;1M Blackwell+Rubin, GOOGL A5X 960k Rubin, Anthropic add, dividend 25x + US$80bn buyback</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY27-Q1-cfo-commentary\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY27-Q1-cfo-commentary\">FY27-Q1-cfo-commentary</a> — CFO Commentary oficial Q1 FY27 (20-May-2026): números precisos GAAP/non-GAAP, segment P&amp;L (C&amp;N +88%), DC networking +199% YoY, China $4.6B→0, mudança metodologia non-GAAP (SBC included), multi-year cloud commitments US$30bn</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY27-Q1-revenue-by-market-trend\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY27-Q1-revenue-by-market-trend\">FY27-Q1-revenue-by-market-trend</a> — IR Quarterly Revenue by Market Platform (recast 9 tri, FY25 Q1 → FY27 Q1): Hyperscale, ACIE, Edge series; ACIE volátil → inflection Q1 FY27</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY27-Q1-10-Q\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY27-Q1-10-Q\">FY27-Q1-10-Q</a> — Form 10-Q SEC, quarter ended 26-Abr-2026 (fonte canônica GAAP): balanço completo, segment OI, geografia, non-marketable securities $43,4B, commitments, leases, litígio, 53-week FY</li></ul>\n<h3>Ainda no backlog (PDFs em F:\\, não convertidos)</h3>\n<ul><li>Proxy FY26 (não encontrado no vault — buscar no SEC EDGAR ou na pasta original)</li><li>~75 research reports de sell-side / independentes (Fase 2, sob demanda)</li><li>Modelos xlsx: <code>EPS Power - NVDA.xlsx</code>, <code>NVDA Analysis.xlsx</code>, <code>CoWoS</code>, <code>Hyperscale CapEx</code>, <code>UBS GPU Model</code>, <code>Jefferies TDP Analysis</code></li><li>Decks pptx: <code>BERN AI NVDA</code>, <code>First Look Nvidia</code>, <code>NVDA.pptx</code></li></ul>\n<h3>Análises (outputs) — ainda não rodadas</h3>\n<ul><li>[ ] <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=pergunta-1-company-analyzer\" title=\"outputs/NVDA/pergunta-1-company-analyzer\">pergunta-1-company-analyzer</a> — why is this a great business</li><li>[ ] <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=pergunta-2-business-evolution\" title=\"outputs/NVDA/pergunta-2-business-evolution\">pergunta-2-business-evolution</a> — how will the business evolve 5-10y</li><li>[ ] <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=pergunta-3-partner-people\" title=\"outputs/NVDA/pergunta-3-partner-people\">pergunta-3-partner-people</a> — why partner with these people</li><li>[ ] <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=pergunta-4-valuation\" title=\"outputs/NVDA/pergunta-4-valuation\">pergunta-4-valuation</a> — why is valuation reasonable</li></ul></section></details>", "ic": "<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Tese de investimento (resumo — provisório, a refinar via Pergunta 1)</h2><ul><li><strong>Transição de plataforma ainda no início</strong>: NVDA se posiciona como substrato do shift classical ML → gen AI → agentic/physical AI. DC revenue 13x desde ChatGPT (FY23). Mgmt vê CY2026 com crescimento sequencial &quot;excedendo a oportunidade de $500B de <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=Blackwell\" title=\"_concepts/Blackwell\">Blackwell</a>+<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=Vera-Rubin\" title=\"_concepts/Vera-Rubin\">Rubin</a> compartilhada antes&quot;. <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q4-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY26-Q4-earnings-call\">Q4 FY26 call</a></li><li><strong>Moat multi-camada</strong>: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=CUDA\" title=\"_concepts/CUDA\">CUDA</a> (deep software install base), scale de R&amp;D (~$20B/ano, $76.7B acumulado), extreme co-design (chips + <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=NVLink\" title=\"_concepts/NVLink\">NVLink</a> + sistema + software), networking (&gt;10x desde Mellanox). Liderança em perf-per-watt: GB300 NVL72 50x vs Hopper. <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY26-10-K\">FY26-10-K</a></li><li><strong>Demand visibility longa</strong>: $95.2B de supply commitments + $27B de multi-year cloud service agreements. Mgmt explicita &quot;visibility is longer than usual&quot;. <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q4-cfo-commentary\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY26-Q4-cfo-commentary\">Q4 FY26 CFO</a></li><li><strong>Riscos concretos</strong>: China (competidores domésticos IPOd, H20 receita zero no outlook), <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=ASIC-vs-GPU\" title=\"_concepts/ASIC-vs-GPU\">custom silicon dos hyperscalers</a> (AWS, Google, Meta, MS), concentração (top-5 <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=hyperscaler-capex\" title=\"_concepts/hyperscaler-capex\">hyperscalers</a> = 50%+ DC), power constraints dos data centers.</li></ul></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Vantagem competitiva (moat)</h2><p><em>Análise profunda na Pergunta 1.</em> Hipóteses iniciais:</p>\n<ul><li><strong><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=CUDA\" title=\"_concepts/CUDA\">CUDA</a> (moat de software / install base)</strong>: ~20 anos de developer mindshare; milhares de apps. Custo de switch para <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=ASIC-vs-GPU\" title=\"_concepts/ASIC-vs-GPU\">ASIC custom</a> é engenharia de múltiplos anos.</li><li><strong>Scale de R&amp;D</strong>: ~$20B/ano atual, $76.7B acumulado. Ciclo anual de &quot;X-factor leap in performance per watt&quot; — mgmt claim explícito. Difícil para qualquer fabless concorrer.</li><li><strong>Networking pós-Mellanox</strong>: $31B+ em FY26 vs ~$3B em FY21 (&gt;10x). <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=NVLink\" title=\"_concepts/NVLink\">NVLink</a> é moat estrutural para scale-up de rack-scale systems. NVLink Fusion (FY26) permite hyperscalers integrarem silicon custom mantendo o ecossistema NVDA.</li><li><strong>Extreme co-design</strong>: chips + switch + sistema + software otimizados juntos. Métrica: GB300 NVL72 = 50x perf-per-watt vs Hopper; 35x lower cost per token.</li><li><strong>Plataforma vertical</strong>: DRIVE (auto), Clara (health), Omniverse (physical AI), AI Enterprise (enterprise). Cada vertical amplifica o ecossistema CUDA.</li></ul></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Riscos</h2><h3>Declarados pelo management</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>China</strong>: H200 aprovado mas revenue zero no outlook Q1 FY27. Competidores chineses &quot;bolstered by recent IPOs&quot; fazendo progresso. H20 ajuste contábil FY26 foi $4.5B no Q1.</li><li><strong>Dependência de third parties</strong>: manufacturing, packaging, teste (TSMC dominante; <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=CoWoS\" title=\"_concepts/CoWoS\">CoWoS</a> é gargalo — modelo separado disponível em <code>F:\\...\\NVDA\\Cópia de CoWoS_02102025_fc.xlsx</code>).</li><li><strong>Power constraints dos data centers</strong>: mgmt descreve como &quot;critical architectural decision&quot;. <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q4-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY26-Q4-earnings-call\">Q4 call</a></li></ul>\n<h3>Identificados na análise</h3>\n<ul><li><strong><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=ASIC-vs-GPU\" title=\"_concepts/ASIC-vs-GPU\">Custom silicon dos hyperscalers</a></strong>: Google TPU, AWS Trainium/Inferentia, Azure Maia, Meta MTIA. Resposta da NVDA: NVLink Fusion (permite integrar custom ASIC ao ecossistema) + parceria AWS anunciada Q4 FY26.</li><li><strong>Concentração em poucos clientes gigantes</strong>: top 5 hyperscalers = 50%+ DC.</li><li><strong>Ciclicidade potencial de <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=hyperscaler-capex\" title=\"_concepts/hyperscaler-capex\">CapEx hyperscaler</a></strong>: atualmente em upswing. Reversão seria dolorosa.</li><li><strong>Transição Blackwell → <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=Vera-Rubin\" title=\"_concepts/Vera-Rubin\">Vera Rubin</a></strong>: risco de execução + margem durante ramp (histórico: Blackwell comprimiu GM em FY26).</li><li><strong>Inference shift — premium de latência da NVDA &quot;unbundle&quot; em agentic — NEW (May/2026)</strong> <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2026-05-11-Stratechery-Inference-Shift\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/2026-05-11-Stratechery-Inference-Shift\">Stratechery 11-May-2026</a>:<ul><li>Ben Thompson articula bear case explícito: <em>&quot;much of Nvidia&#x27;s relative advantage to date has been a function of latency... if latency isn&#x27;t the key constraint, then Nvidia&#x27;s approach seems less worth paying a premium for&quot;</em></li><li>Separa &quot;answer inference&quot; (humano no loop, latency matters, GPU/Cerebras/Groq) de &quot;<strong>agentic inference</strong>&quot; (sem humano, <strong>memory &gt; speed</strong>, GPU &quot;unbundled&quot;)</li><li>Agentic inference será <strong>largest market by far</strong> (escala com compute, não com humanos) — BT prediz arquitetura dominada por <strong>memory hierarchy + good-enough compute + CPU robusto</strong> (favorece DRAM commodity, older nodes, AMD/Intel CPU)</li><li><strong>China angle</strong>: tem tudo pra agentic inference sem leading-edge — Huawei Ascend + CPUs domésticos + CXMT DRAM. Sanções US focam em training, <strong>não bloqueiam agentic AI chinês</strong></li><li><strong>Mitigantes / NVDA recognizes</strong>: (a) <strong>Dynamo framework</strong> disaggregate prefill/decode em hardware diferente; (b) <strong>pure CPU server racks</strong> (GTC 2026, ver Update May/2026 abaixo); (c) <strong>training continua GPU-dominated</strong> independente do shift; (d) Colossus 1 / Anthropic deal (220k GPUs ex-training agora Claude inference) prova flexibilidade GPU; (e) answer inference + training ainda Nvidia leadership</li><li>Cross-ref completa em <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2026)\" title=\"_concepts/agentic-AI-CPU-shift#🆕 Framing Ben Thompson — &amp;quot;Answer Inference vs Agentic Inference&amp;quot; (May/2026)\">2026)</a> e <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2026)\" title=\"_concepts/ASIC-vs-GPU#🆕 Heterogeneous compute — Ben Thompson Inference Shift framing (May/2026)\">2026)</a></li></ul></li><li><strong>AI-generated kernels erodem <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=CUDA\" title=\"_concepts/CUDA\">CUDA</a> moat — NEW (Apr/2026)</strong> <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2026-04-KernelEvolve-Engineering-at-Meta\" title=\"raw-md/META/2026-04-KernelEvolve-Engineering-at-Meta\">2026-04-KernelEvolve-Engineering-at-Meta</a>:<ul><li>Meta publicou (Apr/2026) detalhes do <strong>KernelEvolve</strong> — sistema agêntico que gera kernels otimizados para hardware heterogêneo (NVDA + AMD + MTIA + CPU)</li><li>Resultados em produção: <strong>+60% inference throughput</strong> em ads model em <strong>NVDA GPUs</strong> (ACIMA do que cuBLAS/cuDNN entregam) E <strong>+60% em MTIA</strong></li><li><strong>Quebra estrutural</strong> da camada #2 do CUDA moat (custom kernels long-tail): switching cost para custom silicon colapsa de <strong>anos → semanas</strong></li><li>&quot;When a new chip arrives, engineering cost shifts from writing thousands of kernels manually to encoding hardware optimization principles into the knowledge base&quot; (Meta)</li><li><strong>Combina com Fubon (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2026-04-Fubon-Semi-Outlook-2026\" title=\"raw-md/TSM/2026-04-Fubon-Semi-Outlook-2026\">2026-04-Fubon-Semi-Outlook-2026</a>)</strong>: NVDA share TSMC AI 60%→52% (2023→2027), AVGO 14%→27%, &quot;custom silicon scaling FASTER than GPUs&quot;. KernelEvolve é o <strong>mecanismo técnico</strong> que justifica esse shift.</li><li><strong>Mitigantes ainda válidos</strong> (ver <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=CUDA#Risk\" title=\"_concepts/CUDA#Risk\">CUDA#Risk</a> para análise completa): KernelEvolve é interno de Meta (não open-source), NVDA hardware roadmap continua dominante, system-level moats (NVLink, InfiniBand) vão além de kernels, CUDA continua &quot;lingua franca&quot; do ecossistema, training (vs inference) ainda mais NVDA-dominated.</li></ul></li></ul></section>", "val": "<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Valuation (snapshot)</h2><p><em>Análise profunda na Pergunta 4.</em> Pontos-chave:</p>\n<ul><li><strong>Market cap em 25-Jul-2025</strong>: ~$4.0T (conforme 10-K). <strong>[ ] Atualizar para data corrente antes de conclusão.</strong></li><li>EPS FY26 GAAP: $4.90 → P/E base ~$4T/($4.90 × 24.3B) ≈ <strong>33x trailing GAAP</strong>. Non-GAAP $4.77 → ~34x trailing.</li><li><strong>Mudança importante em Non-GAAP a partir Q1 FY27</strong>: SBC passa a ser incluído ($1.9B esperado Q1 FY27, $6.1B em FY26 GAAP). Múltiplos non-GAAP &quot;forward&quot; não são comparáveis direto com históricos.</li><li>Guidance Q1 FY27 revenue = $78B → run-rate anualizado ~$312B. Se crescer no padrão atual, FY27 pode chegar a ~$350B+ (consenso? <strong>[ ] verificar</strong>).</li><li><strong>Tax rate FY27</strong>: 17-19% (material step-up vs 15.1% em FY26).</li></ul></section>", "pa": "<div class=\"empty-view\"><p>Sem dados de <strong>Historical Price Action</strong> na wiki ainda.</p><p class=\"hint\">Esta view será populada quando a seção correspondente existir em <code>wiki/NVDA.md</code>.</p></div>", "er": "<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Evolução histórica — retrospectiva FY21 → FY26</h2><p>Adicionada <strong>2026-04-23</strong> via ingestão de 10-Ks históricos FY23, FY24, FY25 (SEC filings OCR&#x27;d). Fontes: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY23-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY23-10-K\">FY23-10-K</a>, <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY24-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY24-10-K\">FY24-10-K</a>, <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY25-10-K\">FY25-10-K</a>, <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY26-10-K\">FY26-10-K</a>.</p>\n<h3>Revenue por End Market ($M, fiscal year)</h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Segmento</th><th>FY21</th><th>FY22</th><th>FY23</th><th>FY24</th><th>FY25</th><th><strong>FY26</strong></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Data Center</strong></td><td>6.696</td><td>10.613</td><td>15.005</td><td><strong>47.525</strong></td><td><strong>115.186</strong></td><td><strong>193.737</strong></td></tr><tr><td>— Compute</td><td>—</td><td>—</td><td>11.317</td><td>38.950</td><td>102.196</td><td>162.361</td></tr><tr><td>— Networking</td><td>—</td><td>—</td><td>3.688</td><td>8.575</td><td>12.990</td><td>31.376</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Gaming</strong></td><td>7.759</td><td>12.462</td><td>9.067</td><td>10.447</td><td>11.350</td><td>16.042</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Professional Visualization</strong></td><td>1.053</td><td>2.111</td><td>1.544</td><td>1.553</td><td>1.878</td><td>3.191</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Automotive</strong></td><td>536</td><td>566</td><td>903</td><td>1.091</td><td>1.694</td><td>2.349</td></tr><tr><td><strong>OEM &amp; Other</strong></td><td>631</td><td>1.162</td><td>455</td><td>~390</td><td>~389</td><td>619</td></tr><tr><td><strong>TOTAL</strong></td><td><strong>16.675</strong></td><td><strong>26.914</strong></td><td><strong>26.974</strong></td><td><strong>60.922</strong></td><td><strong>130.497</strong></td><td><strong>215.938</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<h3>Análise da trajetória</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>FY21 → FY22</strong>: crescimento normal de semi (+61% total). Gaming liderava (46% do mix), Data Center 40%</li><li><strong>FY22 → FY23</strong>: <strong>0% growth total</strong> — crypto crash colapsou Gaming (−27%) mas <strong>DC +41% compensou</strong>. Ponto de inflexão latente: Data Center já era 56% do mix antes do ChatGPT. <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY23-10-K#Page-13\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY23-10-K#Page-13\">FY23-10-K#Page-13</a></li><li><strong>FY23 → FY24</strong>: <strong>+126% total — o &quot;ChatGPT moment&quot;</strong>. Data Center <strong>+217%</strong> ($15bn → $47,5bn). Hopper ramp + sell-out de H100. Gaming recupera. <strong>Data Center passa a 78% do mix</strong> <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY24-10-K#Page-47\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY24-10-K#Page-47\">FY24-10-K#Page-47</a></li><li><strong>FY24 → FY25</strong>: <strong>+114% total</strong>. Data Center <strong>+142%</strong> ($47,5bn → $115bn). Blackwell anunciado (GTC março/2024). Automotive <strong>+55%</strong> (self-driving). Gross margin <strong>subiu</strong> driven by DC mix <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-10-K#Page-38\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY25-10-K#Page-38\">FY25-10-K#Page-38</a></li><li><strong>FY25 → FY26</strong>: <strong>+65% total</strong>. Data Center <strong>+68%</strong> (~$193bn). Networking <strong>+142%</strong> (Mellanox + Spectrum-X decolando como segunda perna). Mix concentrado em DC chegou a <strong>~90%</strong></li></ul>\n<h3>EPS diluído (Non-GAAP estimado)</h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Ano</th><th>EPS diluted</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>FY21</td><td>~$0,35 (pré-split)</td></tr><tr><td>FY22</td><td>~$1,19</td></tr><tr><td>FY23</td><td>~$1,19 <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY23-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY23-10-K\">FY23-10-K</a></td></tr><tr><td>FY24</td><td><strong>$1,19</strong> (pós 10:1 split equivalente) <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-10-K#Page-38\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY25-10-K#Page-38\">FY25-10-K#Page-38</a></td></tr><tr><td>FY25</td><td><strong>$2,94</strong> (+147%) <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-10-K#Page-38\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY25-10-K#Page-38\">FY25-10-K#Page-38</a></td></tr><tr><td>FY26</td><td>~$3,50-4,00 (FY26 10-K confirmar)</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<h3>Exposição China — evolução <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY24-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY24-10-K\">FY24-10-K</a></h3>\n<p><strong>Sales to China como % do Data Center revenue</strong>:</p>\n<ul><li>FY23: <strong>19%</strong></li><li>FY24: <strong>14%</strong> (US export controls Out/2023 impactaram)</li><li>Q4 FY24: <strong>mid-single digit</strong> (H800 restringido, H20 lançado especificamente para China)</li><li>FY25-FY26: receita H20 efetivamente zerou no outlook (consistente com o <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=NVDA\" title=\"wiki/NVDA\">NVDA</a> atual)</li></ul>\n<h3>Principais descobertas (novas via 10-Ks históricos)</h3>\n<ol><li><strong>Gaming FY22 foi pico</strong> ($12,5bn) — efeito crypto mining inflou. FY23 crash (−27%) limpou o baseline. <strong>Gaming atual ~$16bn FY26 representa recuperação + expansão saudável</strong>, não é pico não recorrente.</li><li><strong>Data Center cresceu continuamente antes do ChatGPT</strong> — de $6,7bn (FY21) para $15bn (FY23) = <strong>+124% em 2 anos</strong>, impulsionado por hyperscalers e deep learning training pré-GenAI. <strong>ChatGPT foi acelerador, não origem</strong> da tese de DC.</li><li><strong>Networking decolou só em FY26</strong> — $31bn em FY26 vs $13bn FY25 = <strong>+142%</strong>. Tese de &quot;second leg&quot; de growth via Spectrum-X + InfiniBand se materializou concretamente. Implicação: <strong>Networking é o próximo $100bn+ segmento potencial</strong>.</li><li><strong>Gross margin subiu estruturalmente</strong> em FY25-FY26 driven por DC mix. Consistência com moat de pricing power + exclusividade de Blackwell/Rubin.</li><li><strong>Automotive ainda é pequeno</strong> ($2,3bn FY26) mas crescendo 40%+ anualmente. <strong>Vetor latente</strong> — se self-driving ramp-up em 2027+, pode ser surpresa positiva.</li></ol></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>🆕 Q1 FY27 (CY1Q26) — earnings call 20-May-2026</h2><p>Fonte: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY27-Q1-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY27-Q1-earnings-call\">NVDA Q1 FY27 earnings call, 20-May-2026</a> (Bloomberg Live Transcript). Trimestre encerrado em 27-Abr-2026.</p>\n<h3>Headline financials (números oficiais, do <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY27-Q1-cfo-commentary\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY27-Q1-cfo-commentary\">CFO Commentary 20-May-2026</a>)</h3>\n<p><strong>GAAP</strong>: Revenue <strong>US$81,615M (+85% YoY, +20% QoQ)</strong> · GM <strong>74.9%</strong> · Op income <strong>US$53,536M (+147% YoY)</strong> · NI <strong>US$58,321M (+211% YoY)</strong> · EPS <strong>$2.39 (+214% YoY)</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>Non-GAAP</strong>: Revenue idem · GM <strong>75.0%</strong> · OpEx <strong>US$7,449M</strong> · Op income <strong>US$53,783M</strong> · NI <strong>US$45,548M (+139% YoY)</strong> · EPS <strong>$1.87 (+140% YoY)</strong>.</p>\n<p>⚠️ <strong>Mudança de metodologia Q1 FY27</strong>: non-GAAP <strong>NÃO exclui mais SBC</strong> (períodos históricos recast). Comparações com non-GAAP prévias precisam usar a base nova — tabela acima já é apples-to-apples.</p>\n<ul><li>14º quarter consecutivo de crescimento sequencial; 3º quarter consecutivo de aceleração YoY. <strong>Increment sequencial US$13.5bn = recorde absoluto</strong>.</li><li><strong>Equity gains não-cash Q1: US$15.9bn</strong> (publicly-held + non-marketable) — driver do delta GAAP NI (US$58.3bn) vs non-GAAP (US$45.5bn).</li><li><strong>Segmento P&amp;L statutory</strong>: Compute &amp; Networking US$74,550M (<strong>+88% YoY</strong>), Graphics US$7,065M (+58% YoY).</li></ul>\n<p><strong>Revenue by Market Platform</strong> (novo framework — recast 9 tri em <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY27-Q1-revenue-by-market-trend\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY27-Q1-revenue-by-market-trend\">IR trend file</a>):</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>US$M</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Q1 FY27</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Q4 FY26</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Q1 FY26</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Q/Q</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Y/Y</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Data Center</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>75,246</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">62,314</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">39,112</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+21%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>+92%</strong></td></tr><tr><td>↳ Hyperscale</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">37,869</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">33,814</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">17,599</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+12%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>+115%</strong></td></tr><tr><td>↳ ACIE</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">37,377</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">28,500</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">21,513</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>+31%</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+74%</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Edge Computing</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">6,369</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">5,813</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">4,950</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+10%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+29%</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<ul><li>Sub-segmento DC (framework antigo, recast): <strong>DC compute US$60,400M (+77% YoY)</strong> · <strong>DC networking US$14,800M (+199% YoY, +35% QoQ)</strong> — <em>quase triplicou</em>.</li><li><strong>🆕 Hyperscale ≈ ACIE em FY27 Q1</strong> (37.9 vs 37.4) — primeira vez próximas; ACIE inflectiu +31% QoQ.</li></ul>\n<h3>China — base agora limpa</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>🔥 Zero shipments de Hopper para China este quarter</strong> vs <strong>US$4.6bn em Q1 FY26</strong>. Headwind absorvido. <strong>Outlook Q2 também assume zero China DC compute</strong>.</li></ul>\n<h3>Balance sheet, supply e cash</h3>\n<ul><li>Cash + marketable debt <strong>US$50.3bn</strong> (vs US$49.7bn QoQ).</li><li><strong>Inventory US$25.8bn</strong> (vs US$21.4bn QoQ) + <strong>supply-related commitments US$119.0bn</strong> → <strong>soma ≈ US$145bn</strong> (reconcilia com o &quot;$145bn total supply&quot; da call).</li><li><strong>🆕 Multi-year cloud service commitments: US$30.0bn</strong> (vs US$27.0bn QoQ) — <strong>NVDA é cliente de cloud também</strong> (&quot;growing R&amp;D needs&quot;), em escala material e linha separada do supply.</li><li><strong>DSO 45 dias</strong> (vs 51 seq, timing favorável). Esperado mid-50s no Q2.</li><li><strong>OCF Q1: US$50.3bn</strong> (vs US$36.2bn QoQ, US$27.4bn YoY). <strong>FCF Q1: US$48.6bn</strong> (vs US$34.9bn QoQ).</li><li><strong>US$20bn returned to shareholders em Q1</strong> (record). H20 charges/(releases) Q1 FY27 = <strong>zero</strong> (vs US$4.5bn em Q1 FY26).</li></ul>\n<h3>Capital allocation — Board approval 18-May-2026</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>Dividendo trimestral 25x</strong>: US$0.01 → <strong>US$0.25</strong> (oficialmente aprovado, não foi só &quot;indicado&quot;).</li><li><strong>Buyback authorization additional: US$80bn</strong> (sem expiration), sobre os US$39bn remanescentes.</li><li>Reafirma <strong>50% do FCF de retorno aos acionistas em FY27</strong>.</li></ul>\n<h3>Outlook (oficial)</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>Q2 FY27</strong>: Revenue US$91bn ±2% · GM GAAP 74.9% / non-GAAP 75.0% ±50bps · OpEx GAAP US$8.5bn / non-GAAP US$8.3bn · <strong>No China DC compute revenue assumed</strong>.</li><li><strong>FY27 full year</strong>: tax rate <strong>16-18%</strong> GAAP/non-GAAP (vs prior 17-19%).</li></ul>\n<h3>Novo framework de reporting (Q1 FY27)</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>Data Center</strong> → 2 sub-mercados: <strong>Hyperscale</strong> (public cloud + maiores consumer internet) + <strong>ACIE</strong> (AI Clouds + Industrial + Enterprise). <strong>Edge Computing</strong> = devices p/ agentic + physical AI.</li><li>Q1: <strong>Hyperscale US$38bn (+12% QoQ, ~50% DC)</strong> · <strong>ACIE US$37bn (+31% QoQ)</strong>, com AI cloud <strong>&gt;3x YoY</strong>.</li><li><strong>Sovereign +80% YoY</strong>; NVIDIA infra em <strong>~40 países</strong> representando <strong>~US$50T de GDP</strong>. <strong>Parceiros DC &gt;10MW dobraram em 1 ano → &gt;80 sites</strong>.</li><li>9 quarters reposted sob o novo framework no IR website.</li><li>Implicação p/ a tese: Jensen explicitou que <strong>a 2ª categoria (ACIE) é onde &quot;very few companies have exposure&quot;</strong> e NVDA captura quase 100% por full-stack — separa o crescimento NVDA da dependência única de CapEx hyperscaler. Em ACIE, <strong>100% da inferência é NVIDIA</strong>.</li></ul>\n<h3>Vera CPU — TAM novo de US$200bn</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>Vera</strong> = primeira CPU NVDA <strong>purpose-built p/ agentic AI</strong>. Custom Arm cores; co-design end-to-end com Rubin GPUs + NVLink.</li><li><strong>1.5x perf/core, 2x perf/W, 4x density/rack vs x86</strong>.</li><li><strong>Vera abre US$200bn TAM novo p/ NVDA</strong> — mercado nunca endereçado. Visibilidade de <strong>~US$20bn em CPU revenue este ano (standalone)</strong>.</li><li><strong>4 use cases</strong>: (1) Vera Rubin (2 Rubins ↔ 1 Vera, priced também); (2) Vera standalone; (3) Vera + CX9 + storage stack; (4) Vera + CX9 + security/confidential computing.</li><li><em>&quot;All the thinking happens on GPUs. All the orchestration essentially runs on CPUs… We&#x27;re going to need a lot more CPUs.&quot;</em> (Jensen)</li><li><em>&quot;The economics of AI of the future is tokens per dollar or dollars per token.&quot;</em> Vera = agentic CPU; economics de cloud antigo era dollars/core, que não cabe em agentic.</li><li><strong>CRÍTICO: o US$20bn de standalone CPU NÃO está incluído no US$1T de Blackwell+Rubin</strong> — é <strong>upside puro</strong> acima do trilhão. Jim Schneider Q: top 3 incrementais acima do US$1T = (1) growing share of frontier AI models, (2) <strong>Vera standalone CPU</strong>, (3) LPX.</li></ul>\n<h3>Vera Rubin — H2 FY27 (start Q3) + ramp</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>Shipments começam Q3 FY27</strong>; <strong>continua em Q4 + Q1 do próximo ano</strong>. POs já em mãos; demanda planejada.</li><li><strong>7 purpose-built chips em 5 racks acelerados</strong>. <strong>Até 35x maior throughput de inference + até 10x maior receita de AI factory vs Blackwell</strong>.</li><li><strong>Google A5X bare metal = early adopter</strong> suportando <strong>até 960,000 Rubin GPUs across multiple sites</strong>.</li><li><em>&quot;Every single frontier model company will jump on Vera Rubin from the get-go. That wasn&#x27;t true before on Blackwell.&quot;</em></li></ul>\n<h3>Hyperscaler customer datapoints (cross-validation)</h3>\n<ul><li><strong><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=MSFT\" title=\"wiki/MSFT\">Microsoft</a> Fairwater</strong> (world&#x27;s most powerful AI DC) <strong>live ahead of schedule</strong>, <strong>centenas de milhares de Blackwell GPUs</strong>.</li><li><strong><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=AMZN\" title=\"wiki/AMZN\">AWS</a></strong>: starting this year <strong>&gt;1M Blackwell + Rubin GPUs</strong>, <strong>colaboração em Spectrum networking</strong>.</li><li><strong><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=GOOGL\" title=\"wiki/GOOGL\">Google</a></strong>: Blackwell na cloud com <strong>confidential computing</strong>; <strong>A5X bare metal até 960k Rubin GPUs</strong>.</li><li><strong>Anthropic</strong> adicionada à parceria — cobertura era &quot;largely zero&quot; antes; capacity via AWS/Azure/CoreWeave/Space xAI.</li><li>Frontier labs construindo em NVDA: <strong>Anthropic + OpenAI + Gemini + SpaceX/xAI + Meta-MSL + Microsoft AI + TML + Reflection + Perplexity + Cursor</strong>.</li></ul>\n<h3>Demand drivers (Jensen)</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>AI infra spending → US$3-4T/ano até o fim da década</strong> (Colette). Hyperscale CapEx <strong>&gt;US$1T em 2027</strong>.</li><li><strong>H100 cloud rental +20% YTD; A100 +15% YTD</strong>. Customers gerando &quot;revenue beyond depreciable life of GPUs&quot;.</li><li>Dois drivers: (1) hyperscale workloads transitando CPU→GPU (search, ads, recommenders); (2) AI-native products inflectindo — one-shot inference → reasoning → <strong>agentic</strong>.</li><li><em>&quot;Demand has gone parabolic. Agentic AI has arrived.&quot;</em></li></ul>\n<h3>MLPerf / produto</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>Blackwell Ultra swept every benchmark</strong> (MLPerf). <strong>GB300: 2.7x throughput / 60% cost-per-token reduction</strong> vs 6 meses atrás.</li><li><strong>LPX</strong>: SRAM-based, low-latency, <strong>niche product</strong> (&quot;&lt;20% market today, someday maybe 20%&quot;). Grace Blackwell + Vera Rubin cobrem full lifecycle (pre/post-training + inference + agentic).</li></ul>\n<h3>Capital allocation</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>Dividendo trimestral 25x: US$0.01 → US$0.25</strong> (Toshiya corrigiu Colette que disse $0.20).</li><li><strong>Nova autorização de buyback: US$80bn</strong> (em adição aos US$39bn remanescentes).</li><li><strong>50% do FCF de retorno aos acionistas em FY27</strong> (reafirma GTC).</li><li>US$20bn retornados em Q1 (recorde).</li></ul>\n<h3>Edge &amp; physical AI</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>Uber Robotaxi partnership: ~30 cidades, 4 continentes até 2028</strong>.</li><li>Robotics: industrial, surgical, humanoid building em NVIDIA.</li></ul>\n<h3>China</h3>\n<ul><li>DC compute revenue <strong>NÃO incluído no outlook</strong> (consistente com Q4). Licenças H200 aprovadas mas não geraram receita; incerto se imports serão permitidos.</li></ul>\n<h3>Implicações p/ tese e cross-links</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>CapEx hyperscaler reafirmado &gt;US$1T em 2027</strong> + <strong>US$3-4T/ano end of decade</strong> → atualizar <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=hyperscaler-capex\" title=\"_concepts/hyperscaler-capex\">hyperscaler-capex</a>.</li><li><strong>Vera = self-confirmation NVDA da tese agentic-CPU</strong> (Fubon + MS): NVDA agora compete em CPU agentic; valida o framing CPU-orchestrator + tamanho de mercado. Atualizar <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=agentic-AI-CPU-shift\" title=\"_concepts/agentic-AI-CPU-shift\">agentic-AI-CPU-shift</a> e <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=Vera-Rubin\" title=\"_concepts/Vera-Rubin\">Vera-Rubin</a>.</li><li>AWS 1M Blackwell+Rubin / MSFT Fairwater hundreds of thousands / GOOGL 960k Rubin = <strong>coexistência ASIC + GPU</strong> confirmada apesar dos custom silicon (Trainium/Maia/TPU). Atualizar <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=ASIC-vs-GPU\" title=\"_concepts/ASIC-vs-GPU\">ASIC-vs-GPU</a>.</li><li><strong>Anthropic on NVDA</strong> = &quot;largely zero before&quot; → NVDA fechando o último gap visível em frontier labs.</li></ul>\n<h3>🆕 10-Q Q1 FY27 — disclosures novas (Notes)</h3>\n<p>Fonte: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY27-Q1-10-Q\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY27-Q1-10-Q\">Form 10-Q, quarter ended 26-Abr-2026</a> (SEC). Confirma os números do print e adiciona o que só o 10-Q traz:</p>\n<ul><li><strong>Balanço fortíssimo</strong>: total assets $259,5B; <strong>shareholders&#x27; equity $195,5B</strong>; dívida bruta ~$8,5B → <strong>net cash ~$42B+ e marcação de equity à parte</strong>. NVDA praticamente não alavanca.</li><li><strong>Segment operating income</strong> (Note 13 — não estava no CFO commentary): <strong>Compute &amp; Networking OI $53,335M (+142% YoY)</strong>; Graphics OI $2,941M (+79%). Total segment OI $56,276M.</li><li><strong>Geografia</strong> (Note 13): <strong>EUA = 78% da receita</strong> ($63,8B); Taiwan $12,0B; <strong>China $4,55B</strong> — atenção: é por HQ do cliente direto e é <strong>gaming/workstation (produtos não-controlados)</strong>, NÃO DC compute (zero Hopper DC p/ China). Receita ex-EUA caiu de 42% → 22% YoY.</li><li><strong>Concentração de clientes subiu</strong>: <strong>3 clientes diretos = 21% + 17% + 16% ≈ 54% da receita</strong> (Q1 FY26 eram só 2 acima de 10%). 10-Q: <em>&quot;one AI research and deployment company contributed a meaningful amount of revenue by purchasing cloud services from our customers&quot;</em> — demanda indireta via clouds.</li><li><strong>🔥 Non-marketable securities saltaram $22,3B → $43,4B em 1 tri</strong> — <strong>$18,6B investidos em private companies + infra funds no Q1</strong>, e o 10-Q diz explicitamente que <em>&quot;some of these investments include AI model makers that may indirectly purchase or use our products&quot;</em> → <strong>financiamento circular</strong> (NVDA investe em quem compra NVDA). Investment commitments adicionais de $27B. Ver <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=hyperscaler-capex\" title=\"_concepts/hyperscaler-capex\">hyperscaler-capex</a>.</li><li><strong>Other income $15,9B</strong> = ganhos não-realizados de equity (publicly-held $13,4B + non-marketable $2,6B) — <strong>infla o NI GAAP</strong> ($58,3B vs non-GAAP $45,5B). Sensibilidade: −10% nas publicly-held equity = −$3,9B.</li><li><strong>Commitments</strong>: supply $119B ($95B pago ainda em FY27) + multi-year cloud $30B + <strong>future leases a iniciar $32,4B</strong> (data centers p/ R&amp;D, FY27-FY33, prazos 3-20 anos) — NVDA construindo capacidade própria de compute.</li><li><strong>Capital return Q1</strong>: 108,3M ações recompradas por $20,2B (preço médio ~$185); <strong>91,1M (84%) compradas entre 23-Mar e 26-Abr</strong> a $184,98 — compra concentrada no fim do quarter. +$80B autorizados em 18-May. Dividendo $0,25 record date 4-Jun, pago 26-Jun.</li><li><strong>53-week fiscal year</strong>: FY27 tem 53 semanas; <strong>Q4 FY27 = 14-week quarter</strong> — comparações do Q4 precisam normalizar.</li><li><strong>RPO pequeno</strong>: contratos &gt;1 ano = só $2,6B. NVDA <strong>vende à vista</strong> (não tem backlog contratado tipo AWS/GCP) — o &quot;backlog&quot; da tese NVDA é supply commitment + demanda dos hyperscalers, não receita contratada.</li><li><strong>Litígio</strong>: securities class action de 2018 (crypto/channel inventory) teve <strong>classe certificada em 25-Mar-2026</strong>; NVDA apelando. Sem accrual (não &quot;provável&quot;). Risco-cauda, não material hoje.</li><li><strong>China antitrust</strong>: finding preliminar (15-Set-2025) de que a conformidade da NVDA com export controls US violaria os termos da aprovação da aquisição Mellanox — risco de penalidades.</li><li><strong>R&amp;D +58% YoY</strong> detalhado: <strong>+112% compute &amp; infrastructure</strong>, <strong>+204% engineering development materials</strong> — NVDA gastando pesado em compute interno e protótipos (consistente com o ramp Vera Rubin).</li><li>Sob exame da <strong>IRS para FY2023 e FY2024</strong>.</li></ul></section>", "insider": "<div class=\"empty-view\"><p>Sem dados de <strong>Insider Trading</strong> na wiki ainda.</p><p class=\"hint\">Esta view será populada quando a seção correspondente existir em <code>wiki/NVDA.md</code>.</p></div>"}, "source": "wiki/NVDA.md", "built_at": "2026-06-09"};
